<Action id="54657" issue="36060" author="andkononykhin" type="comment" created="2018-12-11 11:55:13.0" updateauthor="andkononykhin" updated="2018-12-11 11:55:13.0"> <body><! CDATA *Problem reason*:  There was no way to customize type of  AWS EC2 volumes that are created for instances.  *Changes*:  added parameter aws_ebs_volume_type for aws_manage role with default value of _gp2_  *Committed into*:  https://github.com/hyperledger/indy-node/pull/1088  *Risk factors*:  Nothing is expected.  *Risk*:  Low  *Covered with tests*:  extended tests for stateful_set.py ansible module   *Recommendations for QA*: * create test inventory using namespace-config.py with options for ebs volumes (optionally you may try default settings), e.g.  {noformat} --aws_clients_provisioner.aws_ebs_volume_size gp2 --aws_nodes_provisioner.aws_ebs_volume_size standard{noformat}  * run provision.yml playbook * check that all volumes created for clients and nodes have expected types * destroy  ></body> </Action>
